Chinese newspaper to call "reformed"
A Chinese newspaper, which had called for on the front page of the release of a reporter who had been accused of defamation, should be reformed, according to a press regulator.
The New Express, based in Guangzhou, had a rare public call for the release of the journalist Chen Yongzhou.
But Chen later on television that he had Bestechungs funds to falsify reports on a partial state company.
Now the New Express will undergo a "comprehensive Rektifizierung," explained the regulatory authority.
"Rektifizierunganordnung" was issued by the Authority for press and publications, radio, film and television in Guangdong.
Preliminary investigation showed that the New Express, which belongs to the Yang Cheng Evening News Group, between September 2012 and August 2013 had several inaccurate reports of the listed company Zoomlion.
"The editorial management of the New Express" was disorganized, the regulatory authority announced in a statement.
She said that they had decided to impose an administrative punishment for Chen Yongzhou "and" his reporters license.
Moreover, we have instructed the Yang Cheng Evening News Group to carry out a full Rektifizierung of the New Express and recommended to identify the relevant officials at the New Express and immediately to review the leadership team of the New Express. "
Chen had written several articles for the New Express, in which he reported on alleged financial irregularities at a manufacturer of construction machinery called Zoomlion.
